21/08/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The death toll from floods and violent storms reached 14 on Saturday (20 August), according to Interior Minister Vasile Blaga.
On Friday, three people were killed by lightning in the northern part of the country, while two others drowned in a swollen river in central Romania.
Some 4,000 homes and 700 bridges suffered damage and more than 1,000 people had to be evacuated because of flooding.
